info.title: sports-stats-web-service
info.description: Web service to retrieve sports data

get.description: Gets a list of all the games for a given day. If any inputs are missing, the date will automatically default to the current date of request.

200.description: Returns the feed(s) for found game(s).

get.description: Gets the game feed for the given game ID or team location and team name, with optional date.

200.description: - The boxscore(s) for the given game(s).

200.description: - The probables(s) for the given game(s).

get.description: Gets the game probables for the given game ID or team location and team name, with optional date

200.description: - The score(s) for the given game(s).

get.description: Gets the score for a game, without much of the extra stuff as the feed request
Gets the game for a given team. Will use current day, unless day, month, and year are passed into function

parameters.description: - The team's location (lower case), e.g. milwaukee
parameters.name: location

Gets a team by its team id or team name and team location.
Gets an SVG of the team logo by team id or team location and team name.

parameters.description: - Optional format input, accepts SVG and PNG; if not provided, SVG will be provided

Gets the team's color palette via team id or team location and team name
Gets the player's current headshot via player id
